Ngizwe Mchunu at the Randburg Magistrate's Court. JOHANNESBURG - Ukhozi FM DJ Ngizwe Mchunu’s case has been postponed to June for further investigations. Mchunu is one of the people accused of instigating the looting and violence in Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal in July. READ: DJ Ngizwe Mchunu’s incitement case postponed to January He's allegedly evaded arrest five times before handing himself over to Durban police. Mchunu has been charged with one count of inciting public violence and two counts of being in contravention of the Disaster Management Act. His bail conditions have been relaxed allowing him to travel anywhere in the country.